Aaron,
Henry J. (1975). Who
Pays the Property Tax: A New View. Washington, D.C.: Brookings
Institution. Chaps. 2 ~ 4.






Bahl, Roy, Jorge Martinez-Vazquez,
and Joan Youngman (2010, eds.). Challenging
the Conventional Wisdom on the Property Tax. Cambridge, Mass. :
Lincoln
Institute of Land Policy. Chaps. 1~4.






Brueckner, Jan K. (2004). "Fiscal
Decentralization with Distortionary Taxation: Tiebout vs. Tax Competition,"
International
Tax and Public Finance, 11 (2), 133-153. 






Brunori,
David (2007). Local
Tax Policy: A Federalist Perspective, 2nd ed. Washington, D. C.:
The
Urban Institution Press. Chaps. 4, 5, 9, 10.






Fisher, Ronald C. (2007). State
and Local Public Finance, 3rd ed. Mason, Ohio: South-Western. Chaps.
13, 14. 






Oates, Wallace E. and Robert M. Schwab
(1997), "The
Impact of Urban Land Taxation," National Tax Journal, 50 (1),
1-21.






Palmon, Oded and Barton A. Smith (1998),
"A
New Approach for Identifying the Parameters of a Tax Capitalization Model,"
Journal
of Urban Economics, 44 (2), 299-316.






Rosen,
Harvey S. and Ted Gayer (2010). Public
Finance, 10th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill/Irwin.
Chap. 22. [雙葉] 






Zodrow, George R. (2001), "The
Property Tax as a Capital Tax: A Room with Three Views," National
Tax Journal, 54(1), 139-156.






Zodrow, George R. (2006), "Who
Pays the Property Tax?" Land Lines, 18 (2), 14-19.






Zodrow, George R. and Peter Mieszkowski
(1986), "Pigou,
Tiebout, Property Taxation, and the Underprovision of Local Public Goods,"
Journal
of Urban Economics, 19 (3), 356-370. 





